# data

**Interface Property**

Custom data to associate with the overlay.

## Declaration

```swift
data?: object;
```

## Discussion

You choose the data to assign to the overlay. It can be any JavaScript value. The default value is `{}`.

## Overlay options

- **enabled**: A Boolean value that determines whether the overlay responds to user interaction.
- **selected**: A Boolean value that indicates whether the overlay is in a selected state.
- **visible**: A Boolean value that determines if an overlay is visible.
- **style**: An object literal of style properties.
